Step 1: collect pre-exsisting documentation and resources.
Step 2: organize said resources in what will be the first draft of the localization guide.
Step 3: recruiting volunteer localizers.
Step 4: have volunteers read the draft and apply it in brief translation projects.
Step 5: collect feedback about the volunteers' experience.
Step 6: open dialogue between senior localizers and new volunteers to discuss changes and integration to implement.
Step 7: implement changes in the guide
Step 8: repeat steps 4-7 until a consensus is reached
Step 9: publish guide on Gitbooks and start using it as a reference for newcomers
Step 10: translate the guide in English so that it may be used/adapted/expanded upon by other communities.
